Honor Indigenous Peoples’ Day this year by spending time connecting with nature and building a respectful relationship with the natural world around you.

More than we realize, we are dependent upon the land we live on. Take the day to explore your local ecosystem. Enjoy a trail hike in a state park. Or paddle down a nearby river or lake via kayak.

Furthermore, be sure that your activities are using natural resources responsibly. For example, if you have a picnic in a park, be sure to leave no waste behind. By being a good steward of the land, we can further the health of our ecosystems for future generations to enjoy.

Recognizing and respecting our symbiotic relationship with the land we live on is pivotal. Honor Indigenous cultures by learning more about the land you inhabit and enjoy being a steward of it at the same time.

Recycling has many benefits, including saving landfill space!
Around 100 billion cardboard boxes are produced every year in the United States. Recycling one ton of that cardboard saves approximately 9 cubic yards of landfill space.

Please remember to place cardboard INSIDE the recycling bin and securely close the lid! Bin lids need to be completely closed. Recycling does not pick up cardboard left on the curb. Thanks for recycling your cardboard in Hampton!

#ad I built a test-generation app after I discovered research that shows test-taking is by far the best way to learn.

@ibm released its family of open and proprietary large language models called IBM Granite. There are a few models in the family, including Granite Code & Granite Language. Granite Code (which comes in 3b, 8b, 20b, 34b versions) was trained on 116 coding languages, and I like that IBM has placed a strong emphasis on data transparency, model alignment and security red teaming.

I used Granite to quickly build an MVP of my test-generation app. I’m no web-app developer, but Granite wrote the code for me: I inputted what I wanted in text, and got working HTML. Now, I can upload my text about what I want to be tested on and voila! A test I can take to help cement my knowledge.

My next step: add RAG - retrieval augmented generation - so I can upload even longer blocks of text without risk of hallucinations (a risk which *all* models without RAG have! Check out my video on hallucinations to learn more).

Create with IBM Granite. What imaginations can you bring to life? 

#watsonx #IBM

This is such a simple activity and can be switched up for any theme imaginable!
.
Use a white acrylic paint pen to draw out your design on kitchen towel or get your little ones to draw out their own picture.
.
 Then use coloured water and droppers to reveal the design! Droppers are so good for building fine motor skills and we’ve made our Inspire My Play ones much easier for little ones to grasp and squeeze than most on the market. Find them on our website: inspiremyplay.com

We had so much fun making this dinosaur swamp with some leftover chia seed! First I mixed a 1/4 cup of chia seed and 1 1/2 cups of water and refrigerated overnight. To make a chia slime all you need to do is add cornflour/ cornstarch. I added just 1/2 a cup as I still wanted it to flow a bit to fill the bottom of the PlayTRAY. If you wanted it a bit more slime-like and to come off the hands easily just keep adding cornflour until the right consistency is achieved.
.
I set this up with stones and greenery from the garden and then just added some dinosaurs! Chia seed can get messy so this is a good one for outside and it’s worth wearing old clothes!
.
We buy chia seed in bulk on Amazon as it’s much cheaper than the supermarket and as you only need a little bit each time, a packet lasts for ages! I’ve found black chia seed tends to be cheaper than white. 
.
Find out more about our award winning PlayTRAY on our website. www.inspiremyplay.com
.
.
.

It’s not too long until we celebrate bonfire night in the UK. If you don’t celebrate why not save this one for New Year’s!
.
Salt painting is so simple and you can adapt it to any occasion, so don’t be put off if fireworks aren’t too relevant for you right now.
.
To make a salt painting you need:
•glue in a squeezy bottle
•table salt 
•watercolour paints
• card
.
Simply squirt out your design in glue, cover in salt and use water colours to dab or drip onto the salt.
.
The watercolour bleeds into the salt and looks gorgeous 😍. Doing this on black paper makes the colours pop even more!
.
.
.

.
This is so much fun and so easy to do, especially if you get the kids involved in the colouring! 
.
Once the kitchen towel has been decorated with felt tips wrap it around a skewer or something similar. Don’t wrap it too tightly as it won’t work as well. Push both ends up on the skewer to make the caterpillar as small as possible before pushing it off the skewer.
.
Lay the caterpillars on the PlayTRAY lid and invite them to squirt them with water using a dropper and watch the caterpillars squirm and grow!
.
Not only does this have a real wow factor, it’s also a great opportunity to practice their fine motor skills and hand strength.

گزارشگر منوتو: «برای اسرائیل مردم با حکومت جمهوری اسلامی متفاوت است».

‌
آویگدور لیبرمن، رهبر حزب راستگرای «اسرائیل خانه ما» حمله شب گذشته اسرائیل به مراکز نظامی جمهوری اسلامی را «نمایشی» خواند. 

او در پستی در ایکس نوشت: «متاسفانه، به نظر می‌رسد که به‌جای تحمیل هزینه واقعی، دولت اسرائیل بار دیگر به اقدامات نمایشی و تبلیغاتی اکتفا می‌کند؛ خریدن آرامش به‌جای یک تصمیم‌گیری قاطع». او افزود: «زمان آن رسیده است که به روشی عمل کنیم که بازتابی از قدرت ما باشد، نه فقط سخنی درباره آن».

.
رسانه‌های داخلی از قول وزارت کشور از کشته شدن ۱۰ نفر از نیروهای مرزبانی در محور مواصلاتی گوهرکوه شهرستان تفتان و دستور وزیر کشور برای بررسی ابعاد حادثه توسط تیمی متشکل از فرماندهان انتظامی و مقامات این وزارت‌خانه داده‌اند.
گزارشگر منوتو: «اسرائیل به مناطق مسکونی حمله نکرد».

‌
تصاویر ماهواره‌ای منتشرشده آن‌چه به نظر می‌رسد آسیب حملات اسرائیل به یک سایت موشکی در جنوب تهران باشد را ثبت کرده‌اند. 

تصاویر ماهواره‌ای «سیستم مدیریت منابع اطلاعات آتش‌سوزی ناسا»، حرارت را از مکانی در حدود ۶ کیلومتری جنوب تهران، حدود ۱۵ کیلومتری مرکز پایتخت شناسایی کرده است. 

اسرائیل اعلام کرده بود جت‌های ارتش این کشور پیش از بامداد سه موج حمله علیه پایگاه‌های موشکی و دیگر اهداف در ایران صورت داده‌اند.

.
عراق و امارات متحده عربی، حمله نظامی اسرائیل به ایران را محکوم کرده‌اند. وزارت خارجه امارات، «نگرانی عمیق خود از ادامه تشدید تنش‌ها» را ابراز کرده است. 
پاکستان در بیانیه‌ای که در وب‌سایت وزارت‌خارجه‌اش منتشر کرده، حمله نظامی اسرائیل را « نقض فاحش منشور سازمان ملل متحد و قوانین بین‌المللی و حمله علیه حاکمیت و تمامیت ارضی جمهوری‌اسلامی» عنوان کرده است.

کمال پنخاسی، سخنگوی فارسی زبان ارتش اسرائیل در بیانیه‌ای ویدیویی ضمن اعلام پایان حمله اسرائیل به مواضع نظامی جمهوری اسلامی گفت: «اسرائیل به تاسیسات موشکی جمهوری اسلامی حمله کرد، تمامی اهداف این حمله محقق شد».

بر اساس اعلام روابط عمومی اداره کل فرودگاه‌های استان کرمان، پرواز ایرباس ۳۴۰ به شماره پرواز ۰۸۰‌ متعلق به شرکت هواپیمایی ماهان با ۲۹۲ مسافر که از گوانجو عازم فرودگاه تهران بود، ساعت  ۳.۲۰ دقیقه بامداد شنبه به دلیل محدودیت‌های عملیاتی، در فرودگاه بین‌المللی کرمان به زمین نشست.
طبق این گزارش، مسافران این پرواز پس از ورود از سوی شرکت هواپیمایی مربوطه به هتل منتقل شده و منتظر اعلام ادامه پرواز به تهران هستند.

مرکز بررسی جرائم سازمان‌یافته سپاه اعلام کرد هرگونه ارسال تصویر یا خبر برای رسانه‌های معاند و مرتبط با اسرائیل «جرم تلقی شده» و با مجرمین برخورد قطعی خواهد شد.
به گفته این مرکز «هر فرد یا گروهی با دول خارجی متخاصم به هر نحو علیه جمهوری اسلامی ایران همکاری نماید، درصورتی‌که محارب شناخته نشود، به یک تا ۱۰ سال حبس محکوم می‌گردد».
این مجازات بر اساس «ماده ۶ و ۸» قانون مقابله با اقدامات خصمانه اسرائیل علیه صلح و امنیت و همچنین «ماده ۵۰۸» قانون مجازات اسلامی در نظر گرفته شده است.

رسانه‌های حکومتی در ایران در ارتباط با حملات اسرائیل به نقاطی از اطراف تهران گفته‌اند هیچ حادثه‌ای در پایتخت و اطراف آن که نیاز به امدادرسانی داشته باشد «تا ساعت ۳:۲۲ دقیقه بامداد شنبه اعلام نشده است».
آتش سوزی ناشی از انفجار در نزدیکی محل دفن روح‌الله خمینی

‌
دفتر بنیامین نتانیاهو، نخست‌وزیر اسرائیل عکسی از او را منتشر کرده است که همراه با وزیر دفاع، یوآو گالانت و ژنرال‌های ارشد ارتش اسرائیل در پایگاه نظامی کریا در تل‌آویو حضور دارد. همچنین رسانه‌ها خبر دادند که جو بایدن، رئیس‌جمهور آمریکا از این حمله اطلاع داشته است.

‌
کاربران شبکه‌های اجتماعی از شنیده شدن صدای انفجار در نقاطی از تهران خبر داده‌اند. رسانه‌های حکومتی از جمله شبکه خبر صداوسیما نیز با تایید این انفجارها درباره منشا آن اظهار بی‌اطلاعی کردند.

شاهزاده رضا پهلوی در بخشی از جلسه پرسش و پاسخ پس از سخنرانی خود در دانشگاه کالیفرنیای جنوبی که امروز چهارم آبان‌ماه برگزار شد، مانع اصلی سرمایه‌گذاری خارجی در ایران و مشارکت ایرانیان خارج از کشور را وجود جمهوری اسلامی دانست.

علی حمیه، وزیر حمل‌ونقل لبنان، اعلام کرد که دومین گذرگاه مرزی بین لبنان و سوریه مورد حمله هوایی اسرائیل قرار گرفت. 
به گفته وزیر حمل و نقل لبنان، گذرگاه قاع پس از حمله اسرائیل به خاک سوریه و در نزدیکی گاردهای مرزی سوریه، از دسترس خارج شده و این حمله مانع عبور خودروها شده است.

به گزارش رسانه‌های داخلی پس از بارندگی‌های شب گذشته در خراسان جنوبی شهرستان‌های سرایان، فردوس، عشق‌آباد، طبس و بشرویه، شاهد وقوع سیلاب و طغیان رودخانه‌ بوده‌اند. 
بر اساس این گزارش‌ها همچنین در اثر وقوع سیلاب برخی از منازل در طبس دچار آب‌گرفتگی شده‌اند.

به مناسبت چهارم آبان ماه، زادروز محمد رضا شاه پهلوی. "به مدیریت اهمیت میگذاریم. موفقیت هر کاری، بخصوص صنایع، در مدیریت صحیح است." بدون شک، یکی از بزرگ ترین میراث شاه، زیر ساخت های اقتصادی و صنعتی ایران است که در یک دوران نسبتا کوتاه و در یک نسل به دست آمد. #تونل_زمان

قطر ایرویز اعلام کرد که پروازهای خود به ایران، عراق و لبنان را به دلیل افزایش تنش‌ها و پیش‌بینی حمله اسرائیل به ایران به‌طور موقت معلق کرده است.
این شرکت هواپیمایی در بیانیه‌ای اعلام کرد: «به‌دلیل وضعیت فعلی در منطقه خاورمیانه، قطر ایرویز به‌طور موقت پروازهای خود به و از عراق، ایران و لبنان را تا اطلاع ثانوی تعلیق کرده است.»
همچنین، پروازهای این شرکت به اردن به ساعات روز محدود خواهد شد.

آنتونی بلینکن، وزیر امور خارجه آمریکا، اعلام کرد که در روزهای آینده مذاکراتی برای دستیابی به آتش‌بس در غزه برگزار خواهد شد. وی خواستار توافق فوری میان اسرائیل و حماس شد و پس از دیدار با مقامات قطری، که یکی از واسطه‌های کلیدی در این مذاکرات هستند، به خبرنگاران گفت که این گفت‌وگوها در چارچوب تلاش‌های مشترک برای پایان دادن به درگیری‌ها ادامه خواهد داشت. سفر بلینکن به قطر پس از مذاکراتی با رهبران اسرائیل و عربستان سعودی انجام شد و این یازدهمین سفر او به منطقه از زمان آغاز جنگ در غزه به شمار می‌رود.
در همین حال، بلینکن تاکید کرد که ایالات متحده نمی‌خواهد عملیات‌های نیروهای دفاعی اسرائیل در لبنان به یک کمپین نظامی طولانی‌مدت تبدیل شود. این اظهارات در حالی مطرح می‌شود که بیش از یک ماه از آغاز عملیات گسترده اسرائیل علیه حزب‌الله در لبنان می‌گذرد. بلینکن تصریح کرد که اسرائیل باید اقدامات لازم را برای جلوگیری از تلفات غیرنظامیان انجام دهد و از ایجاد خطر برای نیروهای حافظ صلح سازمان ملل یا نیروهای مسلح لبنان پرهیز کند. او همچنین افزود که آمریکا در حال تلاش شدید برای دستیابی به یک راه‌حل دیپلماتیک است که به بازگشت غیرنظامیان در هر دو طرف مرز کمک کند.

محمد صادق معتمدیان، استاندار تهران از کمبود ۱۳ هزار کلاس درس در پایتخت خبر داده است. استاندار تهران گفته این استان در بسیاری از شاخص‌ها پایین‌تر از میانگین کشوری است.

.
وکیل سامان یاسین، رپر بازداشتی اعتراضات سراسری ۱۴۰۱ خبر داده، موکل او پس از تحمل حدود ۲۶ ماه حبس از زندان قزلحصار،  با نظر کمیسیون پزشکی و موافقت مرجع قضایی با سپردن چهار میلیارد وثیقه به مرخصی استعلاجی آمد.

.
فرودگاه بیرمنگام در بریتانیا در پی گزارش یک خودروی مشکوک به بمب، تخلیه شده و همه پروازها به حالت تعلیق درآمده‌اند.

.
وئام وهاب، سیاستمدار لبنانی در مصاحبه با شبکه اینترنتی «لبنان وان» گفته است علی خامنه‌ای، رهبر جمهوری اسلامی تصمیم گرفته حزب الله را همه جوره پشتیبانی کند و حتی اگر هیچ کس حاضر به بازسازی لبنان نباشد، تا ۲۰ میلیارد دلار برای بازسازی این کشور اختصاص دهد.
ویدیویی یه گزارشگر منوتو رسیده است از دود غلیظ در نیروگاه فردیس، دلیل ایجاد این دود غلیظ مشخص نیست.
«نیکا فرزند ما است و مادر نیکا مادر ما است»
خوشحالی ایرانیان در استان خوزستان به دنبال بازگشت حاکمیت ملی ایران به جزایر سه‌گانه‌

‌
فاطمه مهاجرانی، سخنگوی دولت پزشکیان در ارتباط با احتمال افزایش قیمت بنزین گفت «مردم در مورد افزایش قیمت بنزین غافلگیر نخواهند شد و بدون آمادگی مردم هیچ‌گونه افزایش قیمت بنزین را نخواهیم داشت». روز گذشته مسعود پزشکیان، رئیس جمهوری اسلامی، در صحن مجلس گفت: «امروز هزینه تمام شده تولید بنزین بدون لحاظ قیمت نفت حدود (لیتری) هشت هزار تومان است».

‌
دکتر آهنگ کوثر، عضو هیئت علمی سازمان تحقیقات، آموزش و ترویج کشاورزی و پدر دانش نوین آبخوان داری ایران در سن ۸۸ سالگی درگذشت. طرح‌های معروفی از جمله طرح آبخوان داری دشت گربایگان برای کنترل سیلاب ۴۲ سال پیش، توسط دکتر کوثر طراحی و اجرا شد.

.
گلایه گزارشگر منوتو از سو استفاده و حضور کودکان در مسائل سیاسی توسط جمهوری اسلامی به جای تمرکز بر درس و تحصیل

‌
آیدا شاکرمی در ارتباط با آخرین وضعیت مادرش نسرین شاکرمی در بازداشتگاه زندان مرکزی خرم‌آباد، با انتشار این تصویر در شبکه اکس نوشت «مامانم ممنوع التماس و ممنوع الملاقاته». روز گذشته علی امیدی، وکیل دادگستری در اینستاگرام از ملاقات با خانم شاکرمی خبر داد و نوشت «اطمینان حاصل شده تا حقوق شهروندی ایشان کاملا رعایت شود». نسرین شاکرمی، مادر نیکا، از جانباختگان اعتراضات سراسری، در ۲۵ مهرماه در خرم‌آباد بازداشت شد.

.

As floral designers, we are pretty good at visualizing recipes in our heads, but sometimes it’s helpful to be able to see your ideas before they come to life to make sure they’re going to work out the way you imagined. 

And furthermore, our clients are often not so accustomed to being able to imagine a design in their head the same way we are. 

Sometimes I would try to communicate a vision to a client but would be met with endless questions and uncertainty and it felt like I was hitting a wall. 

When I learned how easy it was to create digital mockups in Canva, it felt as if I had finally broken down that wall. Communicating ideas to clients became easier, and as a bonus, I had found a new way to perfect my recipes, giving me added peace of mind leading up to my events. 

I created a course so that I could show YOU how simple it is to create these mockups for yourself and your clients, so you too can have the freedom to pitch any design you can dream up, and ensure perfection on wedding day. 💖

Florists: does this sound familiar? You fall in love with a creative passion, you decide to start a business and begin charging for your services. You price out your work, add a markup, and then put it out there for whoever will bite.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Here’s the thing: a lot of us creative types make this one huge mistake when starting out (yep, myself included!) We dive in headfirst before figuring out a strategic plan, like which market clientele we actually want to serve. Instead, we just begin offering services full speed ahead, improvising as we go, all the while trying to build an audience from scratch and wondering why selling is so hard.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
What if we flipped the script? What if we first did our homework to figure out which clientele offers the most opportunity for us? Then, we could tailor our product, service, and price point to fit that market perfectly. Sounds like a game-changer, right? 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Tune into today’s episode and learn what pieces may be missing from your pricing strategy so you can start pricing with purpose and a plan! I promise, this is going to make pricing seem a lot simpler, and selling a whole lot easier.

Two years ago I received an email from a local high end country club:

“I am writing to see if you would be interested in becoming our in-house florist.”

It was a dream opportunity, but at the time I was at a pivotal moment in my business journey. My husband and I were in the early stages of starting a family. I had a vision of a slower life, and I was in the middle of making some pretty big shifts to make that happen. 

My plan was to let go of smaller orders, focus only on large-scale weddings and events, reducing my time in the studio in order to carve out time to begin building a new leg of my business that would give me more flexibility and time at home. 

With my new vision clear, setting my plan in motion, I said goodbye to my existing weekly accounts just days before receiving this email. It was in the wake of that leap of faith that made declining this offer an easy decision. I knew the timing was not right.

With one swift email, I bet on myself in a huge way - trusting that I could build something of my own that would grow to be equally as valuable. Only difference is this path would be truly mine, aligning perfectly with the vision I had for my future. 

Comment LISTEN 🎧 to tune into last week’s episode and get a peek into how that plan is going, as I share with you the challenges, risks and priceless rewards of forging your own path as a creative entrepreneur. 🙌🏻

Getting tired of having to explain the value of what you offer?  In the first couple years of my business, my inquiries were all over the place (most of them on the low end) but I started to notice a huge shift in the types of inquiries I received as soon as I made a few simple changes:

1. I added this line to my wedding page: “Our full service wedding packages start at $______ and most of our clients spend between $______ and $_______.” 

Sometimes when people see a minimum, they cement that number in their brain and think that all their wishes can be met for that price. Sharing an average client spend in addition to your minimum can help give context and set the right expectation.

2. A year or so later, I added two “sample packages” to my wedding page. I called one “Signature” and one “Premium”and each one had a budget range and then listed items that a wedding in that respective price range would *typically* include. Of course there was a disclaimer that these were estimated and each package is custom and will vary. 

This improved the quality of my leads even more. Why? When a client can see what they can expect from a certain price point, they can begin to make decisions about whether we are a fit, and also in many cases they may realize they are willing to spend more to have the things that are really important to them (say, if they feel drawn to the items in the higher package). Again, this gives more clarity than a minimum because it gives context. This strategy actually began increasing my average client spend.

3. Lastly, I started looking more closely at my portfolio and IG profile through the eyes of my customers. I thought: If I were an engaged bride who knew NOTHING about flowers, would it be clear and obvious to me how much my wedding flowers would cost or whether THIS florist is the best fit for me, my style and budget? I started using this lens as my guide in creating more content that would help educate and guide my audience towards finding the answers they needed. In this way, my clients were able to pre-qualify themselves before hitting “Inquire”.

Was this helpful? Let me know in the comments! 💫

1. Hide my pricing 
My pricing and minimums are very transparent on my website. I receive fewer inquiries by doing things this way, but the ones I do receive are more aligned. In this way, I am able to protect my time spent on proposals. Most couples just want to know if a vendor is within budget. So why not make it easier on them?

2. Have consultations or discovery calls with every client. 
If a client wants to have a call, my door is always open, but I leave this up to the client. Couples are able to self-download my services & pricing guide which provides details about our services and answers to frequently asked questions. My inquiry form asks the client how they prefer to be contacted. In this way, I can offer the most suitable communication for each individual client. Phone calls take valuable time for both parties, so I want to make sure that time is well spent. Sometimes it’s necessary, other times it’s not.

(Comment TEMPLATE for the link to my $49 services & pricing guide template in my online shop!) 

3. Double book
I stopped double booking weekends a couple of years back and have never regretted this change. I love being able to focus on one project and one couple at a time. One wedding per week is enough for me!

✨Centerpiece Still Life✨

It’s great to have wedding day photos of your work, but from a business/marketing standpoint I always view wedding day galleries as a bonus. It’s hard to control the result you get from your captured work on a wedding day, as the client is always the photographer’s main priority. Building styled studio mock-ups into your wedding workflow is a great way to ensure your best work gets captured in an environment where you have full creative control. 

Our workshop students had their centerpieces photographed on a fully set “reception table” as well as in a styled “still life” in front of a @chasingstone backdrop, so they could enhance their portfolio with images where their centerpiece could really shine in all the close-up detail. 

@spostophoto showed so much love and care capturing each student’s creation from all the best angles. 🤍

I used to think that having a floral business meant having a flower shop. I thought that growth meant growing my business bigger… and that being successful meant being busy all the time. 

I have learned that you don’t have to have a shop to be a florist, sometimes growth means figuring out how to work less not more, and that having time and space outside of work can be the definition of success. 

Every floral business looks different, and the one that works for you, fulfills you and fits into/supports the life you desire is the one that is most successful. 

I am still figuring out this balance one day at a time, but in this current season of life most days look like this, and right now I am very content with that. 🤍

Are we ditching greenery in bouquets now? Because I’m not sure I’m fully on board.

Listen…I might be bringing the tough love with this post, but hear me out. 

If I’m a bride, or a wedding vendor who engages with florists content on instagram, I’m scrolling my feed and seeing countless posts by florists defending their pricing, splashing their transparency of their business on IG, talking about how we never drink water, and complaining about the amounts of trash and cleaning that’s involved in our work. 

We can do better! 

We’ve had our fun experimenting on reels and sharing funny relatable posts to get views and followers. It’s time to get a strategy in place that is really going to help elevate your business and reach your ideal customers.

Let’s ELEVATE each other as an industry by nailing down a content strategy, targeting our ideal customers instead of each other, and showing more of the positive side of floristry. 

Let’s create more INSPIRING content that shows the diverse artistry of our profession. 

Let’s create more PRODUCTIVE content and shift our focus to our ideal customers instead of defending why flowers cost so much. 

Let’s focus on SERVING our ideal customers and sharing the kind of value that will actually improve their wedding day experience.

Who’s with me?

Instagram is fake so here are 5 things you wouldn’t know about me from just following me on Instagram! 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
(Hopping on this trend was an easy choice because there is nothing worse than comparing yourself to others you feel are progressing faster or better than you. A habit we all suffer from here on this lovely app!)
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
1. I generally don’t feel like a confident expert on anything. While I know there’s a lot in my life I have achieved that I once dreamed of, I am always focusing on the next thing I want to learn or become better at. It’s extremely difficult for me to focus on what I am an expert on and what I have achieved already.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
2. The people who are closest to me know that I am naturally quite scatter-brained and forgetful. I have to be extremely intentional about things like productivity and punctuality. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
3. As an enneagram 9, taking risks is extremely unnatural for me (I avoid risks and conflict to preserve my inner peace) and I have had to work extremely hard to take more risks and go outside my comfort zone for my own self growth and development.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
4. While I’m often told I am “crushing it” or my friends ask me how I “do it all” in regards to being a mom to a 1YO, running a business, keeping up with the home, and finding time for hobbies like gardening and creative projects, the truth is there is not much order or balance to it all. I usually am neglecting one thing to accomplish another, but I have learned to pause and ask myself what is most important in that moment, and that practice of awareness has helped me be intentional about how I spend my time.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
5. I generally am a pretty untidy and messy person, and I can thrive with quite a bit of disorder. However, I eventually reach my max and I need to declutter and re-beautify my environment in order to clear my mind and feel less overwhelmed!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

This is a game changer for any floral business owner.

I get it. You’re waiting for that dream client to come along so that you can finally just prove yourself. 

What if you could take the power into your own hands? 

There’s not only one, but several ways to do this. It’s not a big-break type of scenario. It’s an ongoing pattern of strategic moves with a clear goal in mind. Make it an evolving goal, and your growth potential becomes truly limitless.

Unlock the roadmap from $4k to $20k weddings with these strategic steps! ✨ 

1. Post Thoughtfully - Remember that your Instagram feed is a direct window to your portfolio and where most of your clients are hanging out. Think quality over quantity - share the images that you’re not only most proud of but that reflect the style of client you’re trying to reach.

2. “Be as you wish to seem” (Socrates) - take control of your power to attract your ideal clients. Instead of waiting for them to come to tou, learn to embody the florist you want to become NOW, to open up doors to more aligned opportunities. 

HOW TO GET THE GOOD CONTENT WHEN YOU DON’T HAVE THE GOOD WEDDINGS:

1. Plan styled shoots and collaborations - although an investment, it’s a quick way to give yourself a content makeover. Think of it as a fast track to attracting that next level of clientele.

 2. Create Upselling Opportunties - By incorporating plenty of upsell opportunities into your sales process, you not only offer more unique options to your clients but give them the opportunity to elevate their wedding look and, in turn, elevate your work.

To learn more tips for elevating your weddings from $4k to $20k, including my top 2 strategies for upselling to your clients (that don’t feel salesy, sleezy or icky) listen to my latest podcast episode “Portfolio Mastery: Creative Solutions to Propel Your Success”

Honestly I don’t really know what to caption this post. I wanted to say “body changes throughout the year” but it actually means a lot more to me than that. There were moments this year where I felt really ashamed of my body, (for example when I had to wear form fitting tennis clothes lol). I was also constantly struggling with this overwhelming urge to “snapback”, seeing other mom’s seemingly shrink immediately after having their baby was an expectation I began to put on myself. That self comparison always hurt because I felt as an athlete I should be losing weight quicker than most, I was in the gym everyday so that thought didn’t feel too unrealistic. Most weeks would feel similar to the previous week and the weight didn’t disappear overnight so it was a bit disheartening. To get to the point I’m at now was definitely a journey, an adventure I know that I’m still embracing. All bodies are different and I appreciate mine for how it is. My body has done so much for me and adapted so well to the tasks that I’m asking from it, I’m extremely grateful and thankful. While typing this I realized that if I had to title this post it would be super long and go like- “thank you body for the journey over the past year, I’m excited to learn more about what you’re capable of in the years to come ❤️” haha.

Brand Hatch Creative @brandhatchcreative has crafted a #design that merges traditional #heritage with a modern aesthetic. The dark blue uncoated label, accented by intricate gold foil and embossing, conveys sophistication, while the swirling details evoke the depth of the Highland terrain.

ZIGZAG’s #packaging #design boldly disrupts the #vodka market, offering a fresh alternative to both premium and budget brands. #packagingdesign by @opposite.hq for @zigzag.india

The #packagingdesign for the #petcare cosmetics brand “boop” transforms routine pet care into a playful and enjoyable experience. The #packaging #design for this Taiwanese #tea, also known as Oriental Beauty Tea, beautifully merges Eastern heritage with European aristocratic influences. Drawing inspiration from motifs symbolizing nobility, the design features intricate patterns reminiscent of regal palaces. 

#packagingdesign by parabrand

The visual identity for Noera hotel #amenities is a thoughtful blend of #minimalism and sophistication, centered around wellness and intellectual beauty. The brand’s #design concept reflects harmony between mind and body, symbolized by the spherical and cylindrical forms of the containers.

#packagingdesign by @luminousdesigngroup

Each #beer flavor is represented by #mythical creatures illustrated in a tribal #Alaskan #art style, with bold, geometric designs that connect to the origins of the brew.

Igloo #CraftBeer #packagingdesign by @openstrategyanddesignindia

The #design features a kaleidoscope of #retro-inspired patterns, vibrant colors, and warped smiley faces, creating a sense of motion that mirrors the drink’s lively spirit. Dynamic #grids and electric hues make each can stand out, drawing attention from across the room.

#packagingdesign by @bystudiooneeighty

Herejía Dry #Gin’s design draws inspiration from ancient #alchemy, merging tradition and innovation to create a #packaging that embodies transformation. The #branding evokes the mystique of Chile’s hidden valleys, with each element carefully curated to reflect the gin’s artisanal origins. 

#packagingdesign by @cuplacreative for @herejiadrygin

The brand’s #ecofriendly #boxedwine challenges conventional perceptions through its use of tactile materials like craft paper and #tape, evoking a raw, artisanal feel. With a streetwear-inspired aesthetic, the visual identity combines bold, evocative colors and minimalist elements, reflecting the brand's rebellious yet effortless character.

#packagingdesign by @ourfriendsagency

United Fisheries' brand refresh is anchored in the "Sea Believers" concept, reflecting their deep respect for the #ocean and the authenticity of #NewZealand’s coastal environment. The new wordmark, designed to resemble a fishing hook pulling through water, visually captures the essence of freshly caught #seafood. 

#packagingdesign by @triedandtruedesign

RAGA's #packaging captures the essence of #joyful gifting through a #design that harmonizes creativity, warmth, and connection. Inspired by the rhythmic flow of Raga music and the founder's name, Ragia, the concept celebrates love and growth with vibrant, #colorful shapes representing people, flowers, and eyes. 

#packagingdesign by @boldbranding

Stabburet liver pâté, one of #Norway's iconic products, undergoes a thoughtful #design refresh, embracing both simplicity and #inclusivity. By introducing new children's faces, the design becomes more contemporary and relatable, reflecting the diversity of modern Norwegian families. 

#packagingdesign by @cretalux

The #packagingdesign by @byhuman for this cacao product masterfully blends ancient #Mayan mythology with modern luxury, creating an immersive narrative. Featuring #monkey warriors as guardians of cacao, the #design draws on the sacred role monkeys played in Mayan culture, symbolizing protection and reverence.

The #turquoise #hourglass-shaped bottle, enriched with vivid beryl hues, adds a sense of depth and sophistication, while the thick, solid glass base creates a mesmerizing illusion of shimmering gemstones when light interacts with the bottle. 

Tempus Fugit #Gin #packagingdesign by @thelabelmaker.eu

Brutus Premium Lager #Beer embodies the essence of luxury through its #design, drawing #inspiration from high-end liquor aesthetics. The monochromatic label, featuring a signature #fisherman, is enhanced with black foil stamping, giving it a refined, tactile finish. 

#packagingdesign by @sergi_ferrando

The Summer Watermelon Series designed by @lunghao.chiang presents a playful and refreshing #packaging #design that perfectly captures the essence of summer. Featuring whimsical watermelon #illustrations, the #design reflects the brand's quirky and offbeat spirit.

For Wild Souls' expansion into #Dubai, the #design concept blends the brand's vibrant identity with Eastern cultural elements. The visual identity combines Wild Souls’ bold #patterns with intricate oriental motifs, creating a seamless yet distinctive look.

#packagingdesign by @thehowdyfamily for @wildsoulsuae

Barunsaeng-gak (BRSG) #brandidentity, "Right Thinking," is visually reflected through bright colors, playful #illustrations, and approachable aesthetics. VINJOY! by Vinos Uvalca brings a youthful, vibrant twist to #wine with its canned Sangria, featuring citrus and wild berry notes. The #design emphasizes simplicity and boldness, with expressive typography and a dynamic use of #exclamation marks to evoke movement, #fun, and spontaneity.

Manìball by Casa Octavio brings bold fusion to life with its inventive #peanutbutter #tequila, merging #Mexican tequila tradition with a playful American twist. The label design, featuring a spirited #squirrel, perfectly captures the fun and adventurous essence of the product. 

#packagingdesign by @holystudio.co

Happy to be back with @plmotorsport and @Porsche at @RaceSonoma. Today’s practice set the tone for the weekend. Sharing a few behind-the-scenes moments before we go all out on Sunday for the Porsche Endurance Challenge. Thanks to our incredible sponsors! #DrivenToRace #ReadyForTheChallenge

What an exciting day! Two races, two podium finishes. Eventful first sprint race of the weekend. We had a good start and we were sitting in P2 for a while. Yesterday, we celebrated all those who took on Dempsey Challenge, raising money to ensure cancer patients, survivors, care partners, and loved ones have access to no-cost support services every step of the way. We honored those we have lost and lifted up all those moving through their personal journeys with cancer. 

And we all rallied together for a beautiful day in Lewiston, Maine and around the world for the 2024 Dempsey Challenge.

Thank you to each and every one of you who signed up to take on the Challenge, braving all of our cycling routes, duathlon course, and the run/walk through Lewiston/Auburn.

Thank you to those who supported our Challengers by showing up to cheer them on or by making a gift to their efforts.

Thank you to Mark Consuelos (@instasuelos ) for making the trek to Maine to host Champions for Hope and thank you to Ethan Zohn (@ethanzohn ) for hosting our fundraising awards.

To our staff, LOC members, and 400+ volunteers, thank you for your hard work throughout the entire year to ensure Dempsey Challenge day runs smoothly.

Thank you to @unumbenefits for being the presenting sponsor of our 5k run/walk and to all of our sponsors for making this year’s event a success!

Because of all of you, we are making life better for people impacted by cancer…together.

The dog days of summer are often a mix of nostalgia and anticipation. The days grow shorter and the air starts to feel crisper, hinting at the coming of autumn. The sunlight shifts to a softer, golden hue and the heat that once felt relentless begins to retreat, replaced by the invigorating chill of fall. This transition brings a subtle shift in mood when saying goodbye to the spontaneous, sun-drenched moments and leaving behind the long, carefree days. 

It’s a time when the buzz of activities slows down, and routines start to re-establish themselves. For many, it’s back to school or work after vacations. There’s a bittersweet quality to it all—while it’s a time to embrace the beauty of the changing season and look forward to cozy sweaters and autumn leaves, it’s a moment to savor the last remnants of warmth while embracing the fresh possibilities that autumn brings.

Flipping through yearbooks of yesteryear we were inspired by the legacy of American collegiate style. Our short sleeve basketweave knit polos, and 100% cotton herringbone twill khakis are light and breezy. They’re perfect to take you from leisurely August pursuits to slouching back into your seat come fall.

The Garage Tees. To give our new moto inspired graphic tees a test run, we spent an afternoon with our friends over at 6th Street Specials (@6thstreetspecials). 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
6th Street is the quintessential, old school NYC motorcycle shop. From BSA and Triumph memorabilia, to race trophies, to countless photographs - there’s no wall space to be spared. Opened in 1986 by Scottish-born Hugh Mackie, the shop has been the utmost authority on servicing vintage British bikes and has endured decades of East Village evolution while Manhattan zoning laws have pushed garages out to other boroughs.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
On any given day Hugh along with longtime friend, racer, and colleague Josh Mackenzie, and young blood Oliver Meechan can be seen moving bikes between the shop and its basement by way of a rope and some muscle. Whether you’re getting an old (or new) Bonneville worked on, or just want to talk bikes, the crew’s got you covered.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

In our continued quest to do things the right way, not just the easy way, we are constantly seeking out new ways to reinvent the classics. Sometimes that means trying completely new materials and sometimes that means sourcing vintage materials that are old and rare. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Our Per62 teacore Perfecto jacket is made to break in the old fashioned way. Have you ever noticed that special patina on old vintage leather jackets? The top crust is worn down to reveal a lighter color underneath? That’s because back in the day only the top grain of the leather was tanned. Today we typically use drum dyed cowhide which dyes the hide all the way through. But this time we’re throwing it back. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
We used a special teacore leather with a smooth ironed finish that gives the leather a smooth grain and a semi-gloss sheen which wears down as the jacket breaks in revealing the lighter tea colored hue underneath the crust.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Check out the Per62 in stores and online now. As always it’s #madeintheusa.

We have a saying around here that every scratch tells a story. When you take home a jacket you begin the lifelong (often longer) process of making it your own. It forms to fit your unique shape and acts like a scrap book of memories with every crease and scratch. We wear these like a badge of honor and think our jackets look even better the more they get broken in and develop that coveted patina that makes vintage leather jackets so damn cool. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Lately we’ve been experimenting more with pull-up leather. Our heavily oiled cowhides reveal highs and lows in color variation immediately as the color migrates with your movement. The nature of this type of hide is that it scratches super easily but these are just superficial and the oils can be redistributed for a more consistent color with a little heat (a few seconds with a low heat hair dryer) or smoothing them out by pulling across the scratch or crease from the reverse side.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Dozens of our craftspeople handle our jackets as they move through our factory, so these will inevitably show some signs of the hand made touch when they arrive at your home. Just know this is how we have spent years designing them to look and they will only get better with age.

Our 581 unlined oiled cowhide cafe racer (shown here) is made in the USA and available in stores and online.

Behind the scenes of one of our all time favorite films. Easy Rider starred a young Peter Fonda, Dennis Hopper and Jack Nicholson. The indie film directed by Hopper, was released in 1969 and shot with a 12 person crew on a shoestring budget with Fonda paying out of pocket for many of the expenses, “Everybody was taking my credit cards and would pay for all the hotels, the food, the gas, everything with Diner’s Club,” Fonda said.

Cinematographer László Kovács recounted filming in Monument Valley along the Arizona- Utah border, “Peter was in the car, along with my key grip and my assistant cameraman…The motorhome and two trucks followed us. If I saw something interesting that wasn’t in the plan, we pulled over to the side, which was a signal that we were going to be shooting. They’d get the bikes ready. Peter and Dennis were always in wardrobe; there was no makeup. My assistant helped me hold the camera, because I was doing the zooming and the focus. Everything was improvised. I just shot what felt right.” 
 
The crew purchased the motorcycles in the film through a police auction for around $500 and they later were designed and modified by two motorcycle builders, Cliff Vaughs and Ben Hardy with Fonda giving design suggestions. #easyrider #cultclassics #classicfilmstars #indiefilm #movie #bts

For our new “D- pocket” motorcycle jacket, we are using leather from one of the highest regarded tanneries in the world. Shinki-Hikaku, based in Kobe, Japan, has been creating specialty horsehide since 1951 with a unique process that can take months. The 3oz teacore leather has a rare texture and grain with a supple hand feel. As the jacket breaks in, the black crust will wear away revealing a lighter colored core. This is how jackets used to be tanned back in the day which is why you see so much color variation in vintage jackets. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
The finishing process makes this leather feel soft and malleable from the moment you try it on. The combination of oils and waxes in the leather allow it to hold its own shape while being ready to mold to your body. From the first wear, it feels like it’s already broken in.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
This leather speaks for itself so we kept the details intentional. Mixing design elements from several styles in our vintage archives, we combined our original Perfecto motorcycle jacket’s “D-pocket” with a down pointed yoke, an inverted pleat and a fixed half belt at the waist. This biker jacket is slim and sleek without our signature belt or epaulets and features hidden snaps behind the lapels for a more minimalist look.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
We used Conmar zippers on the 4 chest pockets and added a 2-way front zipper for added comfort while sitting. In the 1950s and 1960s, Conmar was the number one zipper brand for apparel and workwear in the United States. The jacket is lined with a 100% Cotton flannel and features button cuffs at the wrist.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
As always, it’s handmade in the USA and available in stores and online now.

If you know how we do things around here, you know that we respect time honored materials and authentic manufacturing techniques. Deep down to our core, we wholeheartedly believe that nothing looks better with our jackets than a perfectly broken-in pair of blue jeans. This is why we are introducing our first pair of USA made, 100% indigo dyed denim jeans. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Just like your leather jacket, indigo dyed fabrics break in as you wear them. A pair of raw indigo dyed denim is like a blank canvas: Whatever you put in your pockets, and however you move about your day will become the distinct markings on your jeans. These are truly a one-of-a-kind, personal artifact, a woven tapestry that narrates the tale of how you live.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
We are using a revered Japanese denim woven on 100 year old shuttle looms at the Nihon Menpu mill. Due to their perfectionism, each antique loom can only generate approximately 98.5 ft to 100 ft of fabric each day which equates to roughly 10 pairs of jeans. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
The denim is a rich, deep midnight blue color rarely found in indigo denim these days. The number of times their yarn gets dipped in the 100% indigo during the dying process is a family secret passed down through a family business for over 100 years, just how we do things at home. Speaking of home, the jeans are cut and sewn right here in New Jersey. #denim #madeintheusa #americanmade #selvedge #selvedgedenim #japanesedenim #rawdenim #indigodenim #jeans #bluejeans

Experiencing Eleanor's art in person is truly transformative. The textures and found objects transport you to the time and place and where you feel the grittiness and eclectic authenticity of New York City.

"My work has evolved beyond oil paintings on canvas featuring the cityscapes of New York City to also embrace the three dimensional and textured medium of mixed media. My latest sculptural mixed media paintings are the result of true experimentation. I build the cityscapes out of found objects such as wire, jewelry, wood, fabric and more and then they’re entirely painted in oils."- Eleanor Voorhees.

Eleanor Voorhees has been working and selling her original oil and mixed media paintings since 2012 from her permanent open studio on the 3rd floor of The People’s Store at 28 N Union Street in Lambertville, New Jersey, she has shown her paintings, wearable art apparel and a small selection of vintage home furnishings.

The first photo is her newest work using found objects from our factory to create a unique expression of our new storefront. The 2nd and 3rd photos are of her process and materials used in making it. The 4th is a completed mixed media and 5th is that piece in progress and lastly, the 6th is an oil painting on canvas all displayed at the store and available for sale with 9 other works.

It starts with a feeling. When you run your fingers across @horweenleather #Chromexcel, you know it's different. A slightly oily, ultra heavyweight hide that breaks in to reveal the most spectacular color variation and creasing as it molds to your unique shape like no other. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
The real beauty of Chromexcel is its smell.  Around here we've grown pretty nose blind to that fresh leather jacket smell.  Visitors walk into our factory or stores and take a big inhale wishing they could bottle that scent, but we've mostly grown immune to it. There is an aroma to this leather, however, a mixture of lanolin and tree bark that triggers a dopamine rush to the brain. One whiff and you'll be hooked.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
This extra special, smooth whiskey colored pull-up steerhide is tanned using a 4th generation, century old, family recipe in Chicago. As one of the last remaining family tanneries in the US, stepping into their old brick building feels like coming home. Whenever we get our hands on new Horween Chromexcel we try to come up with ways to use their leather that really shines.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
This is our first time using one of our classic pant belts in a jacket, for a sleek and modern take on the style. Most of our jackets have a half belt sewn into the side seams and we get a lot of requests for jackets without any belt at all, some have gone as far as to even cut off their belts! 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
We use a strong snap under the buckle so it won't swing around if you want to wear the jacket open. The only thing worse than being whacked by a heavy metal buckle is it scratching your gas tank on your bike.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
What's most unique about this one is that it's made from the same leather in 2 different weights. The removable belt is made from raw 8-9oz belt leather and the body is full grain 3.5-4oz garment weight leather. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
As always, it's made by hand in our family factory in Union, New Jersey. Click the link in our stories to see more details of the P677.

Our friend @upstateguystyle visited us at our NYC store to chat with one of the earliest members of our sales team, @averjoe. Read their conversation below:

ONE FAVORITE THING WITH JOE PEREZ—

I met Joe Perez (@averjoe) at the @schottnyc store on Elizabeth Street, where he has worked for the past six years. We always had great chats, but never really talked about anything but clothes. When our paths crossed again recently, I told him we should get together and get to know each other a bit. Figuring he’d have a great jacket to talk about, I asked him to help me with a new installment of #onefavoritething. No surprise: it’s a Schott!

Joe is from a Puerto Rican family and hails from the West Bronx. He has a compelling family story, him and his twin brother being raised by their political-activist grandmother. He is passionate about social justice issues, loves to write, and is an avid reader. Towards the end he quoted one of the Stoics and showed me his copy of the “Meditations” of Marcus Aurelius. You can feel his intelligence and wise perspective in his chill demeanor and engaging presence. This guy is clearly a good dude. 

Joe has seven Schott jackets. For this post he picked Schott’s Model 689H in horsehide. “It’s very popular at the store,” he told me. “Four employees out of seven have it. The medium length, 25 inches long, works well. I’ve owned it for seven months now.”

Joe’s look in this jacket shows how important a good fit is with leather.  I think this one fits him perfectly. Paired with a pair of @tecovas cowboy boots (Johnnys in honey suede), boot-cut 517 @levis jeans, and a black Kirkland tee, Joe shows a keen eye for bringing classic pieces together in a fresh way. - @upstateguystyle #onefavoritething

The world seems to be spinning faster and faster. Anything you can imagine from far away lands, is now just a click away, straight from your pocket and delivered to your door. While things will always change, we revel in doing things the old fashioned way. Often we too will find a shiny new material or method that catapults us into the future. But more often than not, we're using time honored techniques and materials made to stand the test of time.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
As global citizens, we know resources are limited and we do our best to use what we have on hand. In a world of fast fashion and disposable clothing, the deadstock wool collection was created as a beacon of timeless quality and craftsmanship. In our New Jersey factory, we hand crafted two of our best selling silhouettes of all time using four universally flattering wools.The peacoat and the shirt collared coach jacket are guaranteed to stand the test of time and transcend fashion trends. Available exclusively online. Order yours today, and bask in the glow of the days when clothing was made to last.

Building fire power to imulate the fast twitch reflexes of the ko’i (rattlesnake), the explosiveness of the Mavit (mountain lion), and the power of the Kavyu (horse)! This how I do it at 42. Our biological age is more important than our numeric age.

Interval Short by @tenthousand.cc 

Momoiyo o skeg uḍ ha’icu t’apedag - Exercise is a good thing for us as, it is said in O’Odham.

Movement is an opportunity to celebrate your current health. It is imperative to be strength-based in an approach to thriving and living well. Build off strength and envision how you want to think, feel, and act tomorrow, ten years from now, and into elderhood. Yes, we need to assess weaknesses in all aspects of health and wellness, but if we focus on building our fire to thrive, we’ll automatically address our shortcomings.

As we age, we lose elasticity, which is central to explosive power, if we do not train it. I train less for absolute strength and more for relative strength, strength endurance, explosive power, agility, mobility, and endurance through various movement patterns. The mission of my movement practice are to be well for my lifestyle on the land with family and community and to contribute to the evolution of O’odham himdag (O’odham way of life).

Thank you @paramountpics for inviting Black Girl Gamers to the Premiere of Transformers One. ⁠
⁠
Our verdict? This is a fun movie.  If you've ever wondered about the origins of Optimus Prime, Bumble Bee and Megatron, then this film will fill you in by way of its comedic and surprisingly high octane sequences. ⁠
⁠
It's a film to go and see if you're looking for something fun and not too heavy to do with friends on the weekend, something spontaneous to slip into your plans.  Will you have FOMO if you miss out the cinema release? Probably not, but it's a great film to watch at home with the family. It's a good watch for peak autumn vibes, as we wind down and decompress at the end of the year.⁠
⁠
The cast is stacked with experience from @chrishemsworth to Lawrence Fishburne, @bryantyreehenry and @keeganmichaelkey.⁠

✨ A legacy built to last

Today, Jean-Marc Vacheron's vision lives on in the Manufacture, still in Geneva where it all began.

It has only just begun…

✨ The Beginning

There once was a creative 24-year-old watchmaker who opened a watchmaking workshop in Geneva... Do you know the start of one of the greatest watchmaking stories? See it unveil from tomorrow.

The countdown has begun.

Understated, and quintessentially timeless.

The new Patrimony self-winding celebrates the collection’s apparent simplicity.  This 100-piece limited edition features a 40 mm yellow gold case framing a tone-on-tone gold-coloured dial adorned with an infinite number of concentric circles catching the light.

This visually simple, circular geometry spreading like a rippling wave echoes the cambered dial surface. Yellow gold enjoys pride of place: on the applied hour-markers, on the ‘pearl’ minutes track and on the slender, slightly curved hands following the shape of the dial. 

#VacheronConstantin #OneOfNotMany #Patrimony

✨ So, how did Vacheron Constantin begin? 

Enters Jean-Marc Vacheron, the Maison’s founder. His aim: to push the limits of quality and craftsmanship, bringing the finest horological talents together... starting with his first apprentice. 

Something is coming...

⚙️ In-house self-winding Calibre 2450
⌚ Hours, minutes, date, and central seconds indications
🛠️ Circular graining on the mainplate
🇨🇭 Côte de Genève pattern on the bridges
💛 An openworked gold oscillating weight revealing a Maltese cross
 
The new Patrimony self-winding is a harmonious blend of vintage charm and modern sophistication. Its circular geometry, tone-on-tone dial, and burgundy calfskin strap create a timeless result that embodies @ora_ito’s concept of “Simplexity”, combining minimalist design with complex craftsmanship and representing the collections’ 20th anniversary celebration.
 
#VacheronConstantin #OneOfNotMany #Patrimony

The Art of Timekeeping: A Legacy of Excellence and Cultural Exploration.

Vacheron Constantin's Métiers d’Art collection is a testament to the Maison's enduring commitment to artistry and craftsmanship. The legend of the Chinese zodiac - Year of the Snake, a limited edition series in pink gold or platinum, showcases the exceptional skills of our artisans.

Engraving and miniature enamelling come together to create a masterpiece that celebrates the beauty and tradition of the Chinese zodiac. This series also reflects Vacheron Constantin's long history of cultural exploration, particularly in China, where the Maison has been a prominent presence for over a century.

86073/000R-H034

HQ da Vez – X-Men: Segundo Advento (setembro/2024) Voltei a EDITAR♥️, pessoal! Com muita alegria, recebi o convite da caríssima dupla Hélcio de Carvalho & Dorival Lopes, da @mythoseditora, pra editar alguns gibis especiais de tempos em tempos.

Talvez eu não soubesse, mas estava com saudade de todo o processo de editar, redigir prefácios e quartas capas, me comunicar com os leitores como fiz por tanto tempo… somado a outros processos que eu já vinha fazendo com regularidade, como revisar textos “sérios” e HQs etc etc.🔥🔥🔥

Aproveito pra agradecer também às pessoas que mais estão me ajudando neste momento de “reciclagem & atualização”: @eric_cavalier, Yuri @o.primitz, Manda Conti (@um.mandac), @diogojprado & Fernando Lopes, sem os quais eu realmente estaria perdido… sem esquecer quem me passou MUITO dos novos processos nos últimos anos, @levi.trindade e @thiaghara e os amigos Carlos Rutz (@drervilho) & @ericoassis (que me indicaram!) 🙏🙏🙏🙏

Quis o destino que meu retorno se desse em uma edição só com traduções minhas, o capítulo final da “Trilogia da Messias”, material bom demais que tive a chance de traduzir em 2011 com edição original do @rogerio.saladino! 🔥🔥🔥

E quis o destino que esse retorno ocorresse poucos meses antes (ninguém edita um gibi de 388 páginas da noite pro dia, pessoal) da minha estreia no @labpub_ead, com o “Curso de Formação de Editor de HQ & Mangá”, que começa no dia 01/11!!👀💯💯💯

São 8 aulas pra falar de um mundo de aspectos pertinentes a esse universo, da História da HQ no Brasil e no mundo ao processo editorial, das formas de captação de $$$ pra projetos à escolha do sistema de distribuição… enfim, assuntos que adoro e sobre os quais estou aprendendo desde quando estreei como editor em 1989…

Matrículas ainda abertas, esperando vocês por lá!

PECAN PIE BITES 🥧 by @hollys_bestlife 

Ingredients:
1 cup dates (soaked in warm water for a few hrs)
1/4 cup pecan nut butter
1/2 cup pecans
1/2 cup almond flour
1-2 scoops protein powder
1 tsp vanilla
1/4 tsp salt
chocolate (2/3 cup Evo Hemp Milk Chocolate, 1 tsp coconut oil)

In a food processor blend dates (without water) until finely chopped. Next add in the pecans and pecan butter until evenly combined. Transfer the mixture to a mixing bowl and add remaining ingredients until a dough forms. Form into bite sized pieces and freeze for 30 minutes. Dip in chocolate and enjoy!

3-INGREDIENT White Chocolate Edamame Bites!

"Stop that scroll. SAVE, make and devour these sweet and savory crunchy and indulgent treats!! If you’ve been following my lil clairebearbites escapades you’ll know that my love for snacking on crunchy edamame is unrivaled. These lil craveable salty snacks are packed with protein and iron And contain way less fat than nuts or seeds. So why not turn the best salty snack into the ultimate sweet treat!?!? These sweet beauts are a lil bit naughty and a lil bit nice. Cos life’s about BALANCE." @clairebear_bites 

Ingredients:
1 packet of dry roasted edamame
16 oz vegan white chocolate chips
1 tbs coconut oil
@evohemp hearts

Method:
In a bowl, simply add the edamame and set aside. In a separate bowl, add the white choc chips and coconut oil. Microwave the chocolate in 30 second increments until completed melted. Pour the white chocolate over the edamame and mix to combine. Spoon into silicone molds, sprinkle with evo hemp seeds and refrigerate until set. Pop out of the molds and enjoy. Store in the refrigerator.

Ingredients:
2 bananas, sliced
1/2 cup drippy pb
1 tsp coconut oil
1 cup evo hemp chocolate

Slice the banana and place the slices on a parchment lined baking sheet.
Place in the freezer for an hour
Combine the pb and coconut oil together and melt together.
Dip the frozen bananas into the warm pb mixture, place back into the parchment paper and back into the freezer.
Repeat with the chocolate and enjoy frozen!

HIGH PROTEIN CRUNCHY CARAMEL GRANOLA by @clairebear_bites 👇🏻👇🏻

"STOP buying store bought granola, because this crunchy, high protein caramel granola is not only DELICIOUS but easy as can be, refined sugar free and beyond crave worthy."

Ingredients- 
* 3 cups old fashioned oats (use gluten free if preferred 
* 1 cup @seapointfarms Pink Himalayan Salt Mighty Lil’ Lentils 
* 1 cup raw almonds, chopped
* 3/4 cup walnuts, chopped 
* 1/2 cup desiccated coconut 
* 1/4 cup @evohemp seeds 
* 3 tbs chia seeds 
* 1/2 cup olive oil 
* 2/3 cup cashew butter 
* 3/4 cup maple syrup 
* 1 tsp salt 
* 1 1/2 tsp vanilla 

TO MAKE- 
1. Preheat oven to 315 Fahrenheit 
2. In a large bowl, add all your dry ingredients and mix to combine 
3. Into a small saucepan over a medium heat add the oil, maple syrup, vanilla and cashew butter and stir until well combined 
4. Add that beautiful rich caramel sauce over the dry ingredients and mix well. 
5. To two large non-stick sheet pans thinly spread the granola mixture and press down firmly. 
6. Bake in the oven for 30 mins turning the pans after 20 minutes. 
7. Once golden brown and cooked, remove from the oven and allow the granola to cool in the pan. 
8. Once cool, using a wooden spatula, separate the granola from the pan into bite sized chunks and store in an air tight  glass jar. 
9. Enjoy by itself, over yogurt or parfaits or on top of smoothies! The options are endless! 
10. Happy munching!

Craving something sweet and nutritious? This High-Protein Berry Crisp made with @grandyorganics Classic Granola and @evohemp Hemp Hearts is just the thing! Easy to make and even easier to enjoy. Try it today and thank us later🍴🍓

Ingredients:
* 4 cups mixed berries
* 1 tablespoon lemon juice
* 2 tablespoons maple syrup or honey
* 1 cup Grandy Organics Class Granola
* 1/4 cup Evo Hemp Hemp Hearts
* 2 tablespoons any flour of your choice
* 2 tablespoons coconut oil, melted

Instructions:
1. Preheat the Oven: Preheat your oven to 350°F. Grease a baking dish or pie pan lightly with coconut oil or cooking spray.
2. Prepare the Berries: In a mixing bowl, toss the mixed berries with lemon juice and maple syrup (or honey) until they are evenly coated. Transfer the coated berries into the greased baking dish, spreading them out into an even layer.
3. Make the Crisp Topping: In another bowl, combine the Grandy Organics Classic Granola, Evo Hemp Hemp Hearts, whole wheat flour, and melted coconut oil. Mix everything together until the granola is evenly coated with the oil and flour.
4. Top the Berries: Sprinkle the granola mixture evenly over the top of the berries in the baking dish, covering them completely.
5. Bake: Place the baking dish in the preheated oven and bake for 25-30 minutes, or until the topping is golden brown and the berries are bubbling.
6. Serve: Remove the crisp from the oven and let it cool for a few minutes before serving. Enjoy!

4 Things I bet you didn’t know about hemp

Industrial hemp, historically vital for various purposes, was temporarily restricted in production despite its widespread use in health, wellness, and manufacturing. The abundance of hemp-based products in stores reflects a resurgence rather than novelty. Hemp played a significant role in America’s founding, offering a versatile resource for clothing, tools, and even fuel. Early leaders like George Washington and Benjamin Franklin endorsed its cultivation.

Hemp seed oil, rich in omega fatty acids, offers balanced skincare benefits suitable for both dry and oily skin types. Its moisturizing properties help maintain the skin’s lipid barrier, reducing dryness and potentially regulating sebum production.

Dating back 8,000 years, hemp has been utilized globally for its sturdy fibers and medicinal properties. From ancient Chinese and Indian medicine to ceremonial use in various cultures, hemp’s versatility has been recognized for millennia.

Regarding paper production, hemp’s high cellulose content makes it more efficient than trees, requiring less land and resources for cultivation. Despite these advantages, widespread adoption of hemp paper remains limited.

Recipe: Cinnamon Sauteed Apples

Ingredients:

4 cups thinly sliced apples (about 4-5 small apples)
2 tablespoons coconut oil
1 tablespoon maple syrup
1 teaspoon lemon juice
2 dropperfuls CBD oil
1/2 teaspoon cinnamon
1-2 tablespoons hemp hearts for topping
Instructions:

Slice the apples thinly and cut them into bite-sized pieces.
Heat a large frying pan over medium heat and add coconut oil. Once melted, add the apples and cover with a lid. Cook for 5 minutes.
Stir in maple syrup, lemon juice, CBD oil, and cinnamon. Use a spatula to evenly coat the apples. Continue cooking uncovered for 3-5 minutes until tender.
Serve the sauteed apples with ice cream, yogurt, or oatmeal, and sprinkle with hemp hearts for added nutrition.

5 Benefits of Hemp Farming in the U.S.

1️⃣ Expanding Agricultural Opportunities

Hemp cultivation offers a relatively straightforward growth process, demanding less water and fewer pesticides compared to conventional crops. This makes it a viable and sustainable alternative for farmers facing challenges with their existing crops due to issues such as drought or disease.

2️⃣ Cost-Effectiveness Surpassing Cotton

As a highly efficient and cost-effective crop, hemp yields up to four times more per acre than cotton. Its faster growth rate, coupled with reduced water and pesticide requirements, enhances its economic viability in comparison to cotton cultivation.

3️⃣ Enhanced Water Conservation

The plant’s deep roots contribute to preventing soil erosion and maintaining moisture levels, particularly beneficial in regions susceptible to drought or water scarcity.

4️⃣Opportunities for Small-Scale Farmers

Requiring less land, water, and resources than traditional crops, hemp allows even small plots of land to function as dedicated hemp farms.

5️⃣ Creation of Well-Paid Jobs
The economic impact of hemp cultivation extends beyond individual farmers. The industry’s growth opens up various business opportunities across the supply chain, creating a demand for skilled workers in processing, manufacturing, sales, and distribution.

Just outside Rutledge, Harold Robinson and Angela Dawson embarked on a remarkable journey. With a 40-acre plot, they sowed the seeds of change, transforming it into the flourishing 40 Acre Cooperative—a small hemp farm and a beacon of resilience @40acrecoop 

Their story echoes the symbolism of ‘Forty Acres and a Mule,’ a post-Civil War policy that granted farmland to those freed from slavery, only to see it reclaimed by white owners. For Harold, an Army veteran and former deputy, the acquisition felt like destiny—a sign etched in the soil.

The 40 Acre Cooperative, now boasting 34 active members, stands proud as the first national Black farmer co-op since the reconstruction era. This isn’t just about farming; it’s about rewriting narratives, providing resources, and extending mentorship to fellow ambitious farmers facing adversity.

Through economies of size, 40 Acre Cooperative is not just reducing costs but rewriting the playbook for small farmers, helping them sustain and thrive. Join us in cultivating dreams and rewriting history, one harvest at a time. 🌾🌍

Ever wondered about the journey of hemp hearts from field to plate? 🌱 Here’s a peek into the meticulous process:

Have you ever wondered where the powerful compounds in your favorite CBD products come from? 

While THC and CBD are famous, the cannabis plant is rich with over 80 active cannabinoids, each contributing to its unique therapeutic effects. These compounds are born in the trichomes, tiny structures on the plant. Here, resin glands produce and store cannabinoids and terpenes, essential for the plant's potency. Through careful harvesting and processing, we extract these trichomes to create high-quality cannabis extracts like CBD oil, rich in concentrated cannabinoids. The cannabis world is vast, with over 100 different cannabinoids, including CBN, CBG, and THCV, each with unique properties. The variety and concentration of these compounds vary across cannabis strains.

In 2010, Jourdan and Ari were college students at the University of Denver. Ari's mom shared the benefits of hemp with him on a vacation, and the two college students went down a rabbit hole. They wanted to learn more and more about the most nutritionally complete food source on the planet. Jourdan and Ari decided they wanted to get hemp in the hands of as many people in the community as possible so they can enjoy the benefits of it. They started making the first ever hemp bars by hand in a small kitchen, and went all the way to being recognized by Forbes 30 under 30 in 2017.

Along with a passion for hemp, is a passion for economic equity and agricultural development. That's why Jourdan and Ari have partnered with 40 Acre Co-op, a hemp farm and cooperative that provides resources and mentorship to disadvantaged farmers. 40 Acres is proud to be the first national black farmer co-op since the reconstruction era in the United States. Through economies of size, they reduce the costs, and help farmers stay in the game and make a decent living while they are at it. Now, 40 Acres produces all of the hemp for our CBD products, using their Wunder x Woman strain - one of the top tier hemp varietals today.

The goal is to reverse the staggering underrepresentation of Black farmers, scientists, and business people in the hemp industry. This collaboration is important for our entire industry and we intend to use this momentum to create lasting and impactful change.

Hemp-Powered Pumpkin Pie 🎃 A Harvest of Health in Every Bite.

For the Crust:
1 1/4 cups graham cracker crumbs
1/4 cup @evohemp hearts
1/4 cup melted unsalted butter
1/4 cup granulated sugar

For the Filling:
15 oz (about 1 3/4 cups) canned pumpkin puree
1/2 cup brown sugar, packed
1/4 cup @evohemp seed oil
2 large eggs
1 tsp ground cinnamon
1/2 tsp ground ginger
1/4 tsp ground nutmeg
1/4 tsp salt
1/2 cup plant milk
1/4 cup coconut cream
4 full droppers @evohemp CBD oil

For the Crust:
1. Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C).
2. In a mixing bowl, combine the graham cracker crumbs, hemp hearts, melted butter, and granulated sugar. Mix until the mixture resembles wet sand.
3. Press the crumb mixture into a 9-inch pie dish, evenly covering the bottom and sides to create the crust.
4. Bake the crust in the preheated oven for 10 minutes. Remove from the oven and let it cool while you prepare the filling. Leave the oven on.

For the Filling:
1. In a large mixing bowl, whisk together the pumpkin puree, brown sugar, hemp oil, eggs, ground cinnamon, ground ginger, ground nutmeg, salt and CBD oil until well combined.
2. Gradually add the plant milk and coconut cream, continuing to whisk until the mixture is smooth and creamy.
3. Pour the pumpkin mixture into the pre-baked crust, spreading it evenly.
4. Place the pie in the preheated oven and bake for 45-50 minutes or until the filling is set and a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.
5. Remove the pie from the oven and let it cool completely on a wire rack.
6. Once the pie has cooled, you can refrigerate it for a few hours or overnight.
7. Slice and serve your Hemp-Infused Pumpkin Pie with a dollop of whipped cream or a sprinkle of hemp hearts for an extra touch of goodness.

Breaking Down The Endocannabinoid System (ECS).

This complex cell-signaling system can be found in the bodies of humans & many other animals. It plays a crucial role in regulating a variety of physiological processes to maintain homeostasis, which is the internal balance necessary for overall well-being.

The ECS consists of three main components:

1. Cannabinoid Receptors: The two primary types are CB1 which can be found in the central nervous system (brain & spinal cord) while CB2 receptors are primarily found in immune cells & peripheral tissues.

2. Endocannabinoids: These are naturally occurring compounds produced by the body that bind to cannabinoid receptors.

3. Enzymes: Enzymes are responsible for the synthesis & breakdown of endocannabinoids.

The ECS regulates a wide range of functions, including:

• Mood & Stress: CB1 receptors in the brain are involved in these processes

• Pain Perception: Activation of CB1 receptors can help regulate pain sensation

• Immune Function: CB2 receptors contribute to regulating immune responses & inflammation

• Appetite and Digestion: The ECS is involved in appetite regulation & digestive processes

• Sleep: The ECS influences sleep patterns & the sleep-wake cycle

• Neuroprotection: The ECS may play a role in protecting nerve cells & supporting overall brain health

Phytocannabinoids, such as CBD (cannabidiol), found in the cannabis plant, interact with the endocannabinoid system. Understanding how the ECS functions can provide insights into various health conditions and how certain compounds, like CBD, might interact with the system to promote wellness.

Hemp terpenes are known for their diverse range of scents and potential health benefits. These compounds are found in the resin glands of hemp flowers and leaves, and they are produced alongside cannabinoids like CBD (cannabidiol).

Some common terpenes found in hemp include:

1. Myrcene: This terpene has an earthy, musky aroma and is also found in other plants like hops, thyme, and lemongrass. It's believed to have relaxing and sedative effects.

2. Linalool: Linalool is often associated with floral and citrusy aromas. It's found in lavender, mint, and other plants. Linalool is known for its potential anti-anxiety and relaxation-inducing properties.

3. Pinene: As the name suggests, pinene has a pine-like aroma and can also be found in pine trees, rosemary, and basil. It may have bronchodilator properties and potentially aid in respiratory health.

4. Limonene: Limonene has a citrusy scent and is found in citrus fruits, as well as juniper and peppermint. It's associated with mood elevation, stress reduction, and potential anti-inflammatory effects.

5. Beta-Caryophyllene: This terpene has a spicy and peppery aroma and can also be found in black pepper, cloves, and other spices. It's unique among terpenes as it can interact with the body's endocannabinoid system, potentially contributing to anti-inflammatory and analgesic effects.

6. Humulene: Humulene has an earthy and woody aroma and is present in hops, sage, and ginseng. It's believed to have potential anti-inflammatory and appetite-suppressant properties.

7. Terpinolene: Terpinolene has a fresh, herbal, and sometimes floral scent. It's found in a variety of plants, including nutmeg, cumin, and apples. Terpinolene may have sedative and relaxing effects.

Hemp terpenes, like those found in other plants, have the potential to interact with the body's systems and contribute to various therapeutic effects. When combined with cannabinoids in a phenomenon known as the "entourage effect," these compounds may enhance each other's benefits.

What is the entourage effect? 🌈 

The entourage effect is a theory in hemp science that suggests that the various compounds found in the hemp plant, including cannabinoids, terpenes, and other phytochemicals, work together synergistically to produce a more significant and diverse range of effects than any single compound could on its own. In other words, the combined action of multiple compounds is thought to create a more comprehensive and potentially therapeutic experience.

Hemp contains over a hundred different cannabinoids, such as CBD (cannabidiol), as well as various terpenes, flavonoids, and other compounds. Each of these components can have its own effects on the body's endocannabinoid system and other physiological systems. The entourage effect suggests that when these compounds are consumed together, they can amplify, modulate, or enhance each other's effects, leading to a more well-rounded experience.

For example, terpenes are aromatic compounds found in various plants, including hemp, that contribute to the plant's flavor and scent profile. Some terpenes, like myrcene and limonene, are thought to have potential therapeutic properties of their own and could interact with cannabinoids to influence the overall effects of a particular hemp variety.

By supporting and empowering women farmers, societies can unlock their full potential, promote sustainable agriculture, reduce hunger, and foster inclusive and equitable development.

According to the Food and Agriculture Organization (FAO), if women had the same access to resources as men in agriculture, they could increase yields on their farms by 20-30%, which could potentially reduce the number of hungry people by 12-17%.

Women farmers are often the custodians of traditional seed varieties. They play a crucial role in conserving and preserving diverse seed stocks, contributing to biodiversity and ensuring the availability of locally adapted seeds.

Women farmers frequently engage in collective action, forming cooperatives, and networks to share knowledge, and access resources. 

Recognizing and supporting the contributions of women farmers is essential for achieving sustainable agriculture, food security, and rural development.

Recent events in the Middle East, saliently the atrocities in Gaza, have evoked not only controversy, but have triggered deep grief, rage, despair, intra-group hostility, and alienation. Psychotherapy has historically focused on the individual personal ego while largely ignoring social conditions & collective currents. This assumption, that we are each limited in our ability to change social conditions, but can change our individual responses and adaptations to them, amplifies the colonialist shadow in our profession: that the individual ego is where all the action is at, and that our role as practitioners is in strictly in supporting the individual self/ego, while ignoring social conditions.

Join Gabor Maté M.D. for a Live Talk & short Q&A, as he challenges this mythology of psychotherapy as simply an individual pursuit amidst current events. Global systems of hierarchy, inequity and power enter our room in every session. As therapists, what is our responsibility in engaging it, while respecting each individual self?

Dr Maté shows that one can take a principled position without rancor to either side in a conflict, that we can support collective healing, speak up for humanity and advocate for a world where the psyche is nurtured as part of a holistic ecosystem.

This event is hosted by Therapists 4 Palestine. We are committed to a free Palestine and all liberatory movements extending from Turtle Island to across the globe. We recognize and seek to dismantle the interconnected and systemic nature of racism, colonization, and all oppressions — particularly the complicity of the mental health field in these harms. We strive to do our part in moving towards liberation.

With summer over it feels like everyone is talking about swaps for fall. If you’re wondering if you need to change your skincare routine with the seasons, there are a few things to consider!

In the fall and winter months, humidity drops and skin is more prone to dryness, dehydration, and signs of irritation. If you’re not already prioritizing hydration and your skin barrier, a few easy tweaks to your routine can help:

🍁Opt for an oil-based cleanser like our Jelly Cleanser so skin isn’t stripped

President Droupadi Murmu interacted with a group of women achievers in the Indian Aviation Sector at Rashtrapati Bhavan.

President Droupadi Murmu visited Sardar Patel Chowk in New Delhi and paid homage to Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel on his birth anniversary. She also paid floral tributes to Sardar Patel at Gantantra Mandap, Rashtrapati Bhavan.
President Droupadi Murmu met a group of students from Dras, Kargil. The group visited Rashtrapati Bhavan as part of the National Integration Tour.

President Droupadi Murmu visited the exhibition showcasing the paintings made by tribal artists at Rashtrapati Bhavan. The President appreciated the creations of the artists belonging to various parts of the country. She said that the eternal relationship between human beings and nature is reflected in their paintings. She urged all to appreciate and promote the rich art and culture of tribal communities.

The artists have made these paintings during their week-long stay at Rashtrapati Bhavan.
