APLAZADO EL PARTIDO VALENCIA-REAL MADRID
La Real Federación Española de Fútbol ha comunicado oficialmente que el partido de la 12ª jornada del campeonato que tenían que disputar el Valencia y el Real Madrid este sábado, 2 de noviembre, a las 21:00 h en Mestalla ha sido aplazado.

“Por causa de la catástrofe natural acaecida en la Comunidad Valenciana a consecuencia de una DANA, habiéndose decretado tres días de luto oficial con suspensión de celebración de competiciones deportivas en la citada Comunidad Autónoma, se ha recibido petición de aplazamiento por parte de la LIGA F, tras haber hablado con todos los clubes implicados. Dada la concurrencia de una causa de fuerza mayor derivada de los hechos referidos, resulta pertinente acordar el aplazamiento de los encuentros que se encontraban programados”, aseguró en la resolución el Juez Único de Competiciones Profesionales”.

The Royal Spanish Football Federation has announced that the game on matchday 12 of LaLiga between Valencia and Real Madrid scheduled for Saturday, 2 November at 9 pm at the Mestalla has been postponed.

"Due to the natural catastrophe that has occurred in the Comunidad Valenciana as a result of a hurricane, having decreed three days of official mourning with the suspension of sporting competitions in the cited autonomous region, a request for a postponement has been received from the LIGA F, after speaking with all the clubs involved. In the light of the circumstances of force majeure arising from the events referred to above, it is necessary to postpone the matches scheduled to take place,” said the judge for professional competitions in the statement.

Pamper your hair this #manecaremonday with a DIY mask packed with natural goodness! 🌱✨ Treat your tresses to this blend for extra strength and shine. Your hair will thank you!

DIY Aloe Vera, Egg White, and Righteous Roots Oil Hair Mask

Ingredients & Benefits:

	💚Aloe Vera: Hydrates and soothes the scalp, promoting healthy hair growth.

	💚Egg White: Packed with protein, strengthens hair strands and adds shine.
	💚 Righteous Roots Oil: Nourishes the scalp, reduces frizz, and improves hair texture.

Directions:

	🤍Prepare the Aloe Vera:
 •Cut off the sides and ends of the aloe vera leaf. 
 • Slice the leaf in half lengthwise. Scoop out the clear gel and add it to a blender.

	🤍Add Egg White:
 •Crack an egg and separate the egg white.
	•	Add only the egg white to the blender.

	🤍Add Righteous Roots Oil:
	•	Add a few drops of Righteous Roots Oil into the mixture.

	🤍Blend and Apply:
	•	Blend the mixture until it’s smooth.
	•	Apply the mask to your hair, focusing on the scalp and ends.
	•	Let it sit for 20 minutes.

	🤍Rinse and Wash:
	•	Rinse thoroughly with water.
	•	Follow with the Righteous Roots Wash Day Line for a complete cleanse.

The cooler fall 🍂weather brings dry, cold air, which can make your hair frizzy, brittle, and totally unmanageable. Here are some tips to include in your routine. 

🍁 𝐇𝐨𝐭 𝐎𝐢𝐥 𝐓𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐭𝐦𝐞𝐧𝐭 - Warm up a cup of water, place your bottle of @righteousrootsoils in it and let it sit for a few minutes. Apply the warm oil from root to ends, cover with a shower cap and wait at least 30 minutes before rinsing. 

🍁 𝐃𝐞𝐞𝐩 𝐂𝐨𝐧𝐝𝐢𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧 : For a more intense treatment add a few drops of oil to your favorite deep conditioner, cover with a plastic cap and wait at least 30 minutes before rinsing.

🍁 𝐒𝐜𝐚𝐥𝐩 𝐌𝐚𝐬𝐬𝐚𝐠𝐞 : At least 2-3 days per week use just a few drops of oil on your fingertips or scalp massager to massage and stimulate the scalp. Scalp massaging not only promotes hair growth but can also relieve tension and prevent your scalp from getting dry during the cold season.
.

🦠✨ Probiotics for Pets! Not all probiotics are created equally, so here are our top picks to boost your pet’s gut health! 🐾👇

1. Raw Goat Milk Kefir: Naturally packed with vitamins and minerals, this kefir is ideal for picky dogs and cats! It’s made from Canadian goat milk and contains billions of live probiotics, plus it’s lactose-free for easy digestion. 🥛💧

2. Thrive Pro-Gut: In powder form, this digestive booster contains probiotics, prebiotics, and digestive enzymes! Perfect for pets on dry, raw, or wet diets, it features 10 probiotic strains and 6 enzymes for optimal nutrient absorption. 🌾🐕🐈

3. NaturVet Evolutions: For dogs, these tasty soft chews or single-dose sachets come with multiple probiotic strains, enzymes, and superfoods like bone broth and anchovies. Great for picky pups! 🍖🐶

When choosing a probiotic, don’t settle for the first option—check for:

- No artificial flavors or sweeteners❌🍬
- Multiple probiotic strains 🦠 for full digestive support
- A high CFU count (usually found on the product’s packaging or website)
From allergy support to yeast overgrowth to digestion aid, probiotics can do wonders for your furry friend!

The bald eagle is the largest bird of prey in Canada and only lives natively in North America.  The term “eagle eye” is due to them being able to see four to seven times farther than humans.  This is necessary as their long, spectacular wings carry them up to 10,000 feet in the air while they search for food.  While they usually fly at speeds of 64 – 113 km/h they have been recorded to fly as fast as 160 km/h when they need to!

🖤 Embrace Your Glow: The Beauty of Pigmentation 🖤

In a world that often tries to dictate beauty standards, we want to take a moment to celebrate the uniqueness that each of us carries – our skin tells a story, and every pigment is a chapter. 🌈✨

Pigmentation, in all its forms, is a beautiful reminder that our differences make us who we are. Whether it’s a sun-kissed glow, freckles that dance across our cheeks, or deeper tones that reflect our rich heritage, every mark is a testament to our journey. 

For so many, unwanted pigmentation can feel like a source of insecurity, but it’s time to shift the narrative. Let’s empower ourselves to love our skin in its entirety – the good, the bad, and the beautifully imperfect. 💪🏽💖

At Sircuit Skin, we stand with you in your journey toward self-acceptance. Our products are designed not just to enhance your skin, but to amplify your confidence. Let’s celebrate our pigment, harness its power, and shine brighter than ever! 🌟

So many of the parents who have messaged me about their estrangements or joined our groups @callinghome.co speak about the good times they had with their child. They send me lists of positive things they did, fun times they had, and how they don’t understand how they got here after all of that good. I believe a lot of that good did exist and likely still does.

I look at my own children in the middle of a happy moment and think, “wow I hope they remember this.” And I also know they won’t remember a lot of it. They won’t know what went into so much of this. Or, some of the things I’m doing simply won’t matter in the end. They’re going to remember things from their own perspective - the good, the bad, and the neutral.

But I think I am starting to understand more of what is happening here. Maybe some parents assume that if we focus on the “good” we can erase the bad. If we look at all the things we did do, we can forget about things like how the divorce impacted our kid, or how they were hurt by our addiction, or how they got shuffled around from school to school. It’s possible that we’re trying to do all this “good” so we can cancel out the bad and absolve ourselves from ever having to be accountable. Maybe this feels easier than holding space for the reality that we all mess up. We all do good and we all hurt people, including our own kids. Some cause way more harm than others.

In my experience, the only way to truly make up for the hurts we’ve caused (indirectly or directly) is to really sit with the person, listen to them, try to understand, and find a way to do better in the future. Nothing else works as well as this. No one is all good or all bad. Everyone can grow. Not everyone has the opportunity to grow and not everyone will.

If this does not apply to your situation, that is ok. There are of course marriages and co-parenting dynamics where people are unfairly attacked by the other parent. I’m not speaking about those dynamics. This post is specifically for adult children who have dealt with this.

When I work with adult children who are becoming estranged from a parent, many of them report that that parent accused them of being brainwashed. The only reason they feel this way is because the other parent convinced them. There’s no way they came to this conclusion on their own.

The adult child is left utterly confused by this because they witnessed the bad behavior. They saw the domestic v*olence, the constant criticism, the yelling and fighting, and/or the infidelity, the ab*se, substance usage, etc. They saw this parent’s actions and they didn’t like how it made them feel. The way this parent showed up in the home is what broke the trust and safety in the relationship. It wasn’t what their other parent told them. It was what they witnessed.

If you’re an adult who is navigating a difficult dynamic with a parent, did you experience this? What was it like?

It seems like we are the first generation thinking through these transitions and how we want to navigate them.

If you are a parent who had to raise your child in an environment like this and make these choices, immense empathy for you. This is not black and white. 

There are so many reasons why a parent may do this - all of them extremely understandable and valid. They may be protecting themselves and their children from other violence. They may think that if they call out behavior, they'll be harmed financially, physically, or emotionally, so they choose to stay quiet. It makes sense why they do this and it's a well-understood phenomenon. Many adults are victims in their own homes, just trying to survive. This explains the situation. It doesn't change how it may have impacted you.

If you are an adult who is trying to hold empathy and work through how this has impacted you today, this is why you join the family cyclebreakers club @callinghome.co. We can understand why people end up in these situations and so much of it is bad luck, circumstances, and choices that didn't work out the way we thought they would.

And, I know for a fact, that if you've lived this, you do not want to repeat it.

Cam’s Kindness Week is back 🙌

On Monday, Cam Heyward opened the newest location for Craig’s Closet at West Mifflin High School. 

Craig’s Closet is a program that he began in honor of his late father, Craig “Ironhead” Heyward, that provides high school boys in the Pittsburgh area with free dress clothes for interviews, internships, banquets, & more.

Cam’s Kindness Week then continued with a visit to The Caring Place, a center for grieving children and their families. 

He spoke with the kids about his own journey with grief following the loss of his father, Craig “Ironhead” Heyward. He also worked with the kids to make remembrance candles to honor their loved ones they have lost.

I took a solo adventure to Cincinnati to attend BLINK- 

BLINK is a celebration that nurtures community and connection through public art. This festival features over 80 interactive installations by dozens of international muralists, light installation and projection artists. These local, national, and international artists create a living, breathing event that you really have to see to believe.

I left feeling motivated and inspired.

Special thanks to artist @vincefraser for the inspiration to attend.

Fun was had at the opening reception for @chicagogamespace  INSERT COIN: Inside Midway’s Arcade Revolution at Cleve Carney Museum of Art (CCMA). I encourage yall to check it out.

I got to fist fight @insertcoindoc  director and exhibition co-organizer @thejoshtsui and give Ed Boon an epic high five!

This exhibition is about the stories of Williams and Bally Midway in the 1980s, and Midway, the maker of Mortal Kombat and NBA Jam, in the 1990s.

Super thanks to @jkinkley1 for being so freaking awesome and welcoming! I felt at home with how nice everyone was.
